title: Greyhounds and #5 Hawks Score Shutouts
text:
Greyhounds and #5 Hawks Score Shutouts 
By Norman Seawright III October 1, 2015 Updated Oct 1, 2015 at 10:35 PM CDT 
(NNCNOW.com) -- In high school boys soccer, No. 5 Hermantown remains undefeated, while Duluth East denied Duluth Marshall city bragging rights (along with its first win of the season)â€”in both games, it was a tale of two keepers. 
East's goalie Corrado Rosato helped turned away every Hilltopper shot as the rest of the Greyhounds netted six goals to shut out Marshall 6-0. The Hilltoppers will host Chisago Lakes on October 3 at 2:00 PM, while Duluth East hosts Cloquet at 8:00 PM on October 5. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
Within twenty minutes, the Hawks had scored four goals against the visiting Superior team; Hermantown picked up two more and, behind Ricardo Stage's performance in goal, shut out the Spartans 6-0. Hermantown will host Cloquet at 11:00 AM on October 3, while the Spartans return to action on October 5 to host Hayward at 4:30 PM.
